  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5966ba09",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Treinar o modelo FINAL com os melhores hiperparametros\n",
    "\n",
    "Agora que sabemos a melhor combinacao, treinamos um **modelo novo** com:\n",
    "- Os hiperparametros do melhor trial\n",
    "- **Mais epocas** (80 em vez de 25), porque sabemos que e uma boa combinacao\n",
    "- ReduceLROnPlateau adicional, pra refinar nos finais"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7be093a0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# RECRIAR O MODELO COM OS MELHORES HPs\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# FixedTrial e um \"trial fake\" que sempre devolve os valores que passamos.\n",
    "# Permite reusar a funcao build_cnn (que espera um trial) sem reescrever.\n",
    "fixed_trial = optuna.trial.FixedTrial(study.best_params)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Constroi o modelo com os melhores HPs\n",
    "best_model, best_batch_size = build_cnn(fixed_trial, n_wave=n_wave)\n",
    "\n",
    "# .summary() mostra a arquitetura completa: camadas, shapes, parametros\n",
    "best_model.summary()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2c79bf22",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# TREINO FINAL\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# FINAL_EPOCHS vem da celula `parameters` la em cima (default 80).\n",
    "# ReduceLR refina o lr no final do treino.\n",
    "final_history = best_model.fit(\n",
    "    X_train, y_train,\n",
    "    validation_data=(X_val, y_val),\n",
    "    epochs=FINAL_EPOCHS,            # mais epocas pq sabemos que sao bons HPs\n",
    "    batch_size=best_batch_size,\n",
    "    callbacks=[\n",
    "        # EarlyStopping: para se val_loss nao melhorar em 15 epocas\n",
    "        keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(\n",
    "            monitor=\"val_loss\",\n",
    "            patience=15,\n",
    "            restore_best_weights=True,\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "        # ReduceLROnPlateau: reduz lr * 0.5 se val_loss estagnar 7 epocas.\n",
    "        # Isso ajuda no \"fine tuning\" final do treino.\n",
    "        keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(\n",
    "            monitor=\"val_loss\",\n",
    "            factor=0.5,\n",
    "            patience=7,\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    verbose=2,   # 1 linha por epoca (verbose=1 seria barra de progresso, polui muito)\n",
    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "157e6c07",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Avaliar no test\n",
    "\n",
    "Esta e a **primeira e unica vez** que tocamos no `X_test`. Os numeros aqui sao a metrica \"real\" do modelo, nao influenciada por HPO nem early stopping.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Definicoes\n",
    "\n",
    "- `delta_z = (z_pred - z_true) / (1 + z_true)` \u2014 erro normalizado pelo redshift\n",
    "- `bias` = mediana de `delta_z` (deveria ser ~0 se nao ha vi\u00e9s sistematico)\n",
    "- `sigma_NMAD = 1.4826 * MAD(delta_z)` \u2014 \"desvio padrao robusto\" (ignora outliers)\n",
    "- `outliers (|delta_z|>0.15)` \u2014 % de catastroficos (z previsto muito errado)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "f269df95",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# PREDICOES NO TEST\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# .predict roda o modelo nos dados (sem treinar).\n",
    "# .ravel() achata o array (de (N, 1) para (N,)).\n",
    "y_pred_test = best_model.predict(X_test, verbose=0).ravel()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# CALCULAR AS METRICAS\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# delta_z normalizado: convencao da literatura de photo-z.\n",
    "delta_z = (y_pred_test - y_test) / (1 + y_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# MAE: erro absoluto medio\n",
    "mae = np.mean(np.abs(y_pred_test - y_test))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bias: vi\u00e9s sistematico. Se positivo, modelo super-prevendo z. Se negativo, sub-prevendo.\n",
    "bias = np.median(delta_z)\n",
    "\n",
    "# sigma_NMAD: \"desvio padrao robusto\"\n",
    "# - MAD = Median Absolute Deviation = mediana(|delta_z - mediana(delta_z)|)\n",
    "# - 1.4826 e a constante de Tukey: pra distribuicao normal, sigma_NMAD == sigma usual.\n",
    "# - Robusto: ignora caudas pesadas (catastroficos nao inflam o numero).\n",
    "sigma_nmad = 1.4826 * np.median(np.abs(delta_z - bias))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Outliers: fracao com erro maior que threshold.\n",
    "# 0.05 = 5% errado (mais estrito).\n",
    "# 0.15 = padrao da literatura photo-z para \"catastroficos\".\n",
    "outliers_05 = 100 * np.mean(np.abs(delta_z) > 0.05)\n",
    "outliers_15 = 100 * np.mean(np.abs(delta_z) > 0.15)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# REPORTAR\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "print(f\"RESULTADO FINAL (test set, n={len(y_test):,})\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "print(f\"  MAE                  : {mae:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  bias                 : {bias:+.2e}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  sigma_NMAD           : {sigma_nmad:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  outliers (|>0.05|)   : {outliers_05:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"  outliers (|>0.15|)   : {outliers_15:.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f9a13de5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Plot dos resultados"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "27e3e246",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# PLOTS DO MODELO FINAL \u2014 2x2 grid\n",
    "# ============================================================\n",
    "# (a) Curvas de treino    \u2014 diagnostica overfit\n",
    "# (b) z_pred vs z_real    \u2014 visualiza acuracia\n",
    "# (c) Histograma \u0394z/(1+z) \u2014 distribuicao dos residuos, sigma_NMAD visualizado\n",
    "# (d) \u0394z/(1+z) vs z_real  \u2014 vies em funcao do redshift\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_dir = RESULTS_DIR / OBJECT_TYPE / \"cnn_optuna_simples\" / \"plots\"\n",
    "plot_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- (a) Curvas de treino: train vs val ao longo das epocas ---\n",
    "# Idealmente, train_loss e val_loss caem juntos.\n",
    "# Se val sobe enquanto train cai -> OVERFITTING.\n",
    "axes[0, 0].plot(final_history.history[\"loss\"],     label=\"train\", lw=2)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].plot(final_history.history[\"val_loss\"], label=\"val\",   lw=2)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[0, 0].set_ylabel(\"MAE\")\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title(\"(a) Curvas de treino do modelo final\")\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "axes[0, 0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- (b) z_pred vs z_real (hexbin com densidade) ---\n",
    "# Hexbin mostra a CONCENTRACAO de pontos (melhor que scatter pra N grande).\n",
    "# Reta vermelha y=x = predicao perfeita.\n",
    "hb = axes[0, 1].hexbin(y_test, y_pred_test, gridsize=40, cmap=\"viridis\", mincnt=1)\n",
    "axes[0, 1].plot([y_test.min(), y_test.max()],\n",
    "                [y_test.min(), y_test.max()], \"r--\", lw=1.5, label=\"ideal (y=x)\")\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_xlabel(\"z_real\"); axes[0, 1].set_ylabel(\"z_predito\")\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_title(f\"(b) z_pred vs z_real  (sigma_NMAD = {sigma_nmad:.4f})\")\n",
    "axes[0, 1].legend()\n",
    "plt.colorbar(hb, ax=axes[0, 1], label=\"# galaxias\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- (c) Histograma dos residuos \u0394z/(1+z) ---\n",
    "# Mostra a forma da distribuicao dos erros. Deve ser:\n",
    "#   - centrado em zero (bias pequeno)\n",
    "#   - estreito (sigma_NMAD pequeno)\n",
    "#   - sem caudas pesadas (poucos outliers)\n",
    "axes[1, 0].hist(np.clip(delta_z, -0.3, 0.3), bins=80,\n",
    "                color=\"steelblue\", alpha=0.85, edgecolor=\"black\", lw=0.3)\n",
    "axes[1, 0].axvline(bias, color=\"red\", lw=2, label=f\"bias = {bias:+.4f}\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].axvline(bias + sigma_nmad, color=\"orange\", lw=1.2, ls=\"--\",\n",
    "                   label=f\"\u00b1sigma_NMAD = {sigma_nmad:.4f}\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].axvline(bias - sigma_nmad, color=\"orange\", lw=1.2, ls=\"--\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].axvline(+0.15, color=\"darkred\", lw=1.2, ls=\":\", label=\"\u00b10.15 (outlier)\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].axvline(-0.15, color=\"darkred\", lw=1.2, ls=\":\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_xlabel(\"\u0394z / (1 + z)\"); axes[1, 0].set_ylabel(\"# galaxias\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_title(f\"(c) Residuos  (outliers |\u0394z|>0.15: {outliers_15:.2f}%)\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].legend(fontsize=9, loc=\"upper right\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_xlim(-0.3, 0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- (d) \u0394z/(1+z) vs z_real (densidade) ---\n",
    "# Mostra se ha BIAS DEPENDENTE DE Z (ex: subestimando z alto).\n",
    "# Linha horizontal em 0 = sem residuo.\n",
    "# Bandas \u00b1sigma_NMAD em laranja, \u00b10.15 (outlier threshold) em vermelho.\n",
    "hb2 = axes[1, 1].hexbin(y_test, np.clip(delta_z, -0.3, 0.3),\n",
    "                        gridsize=40, cmap=\"magma\", mincnt=1)\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axhline(0,          color=\"white\",  lw=1.5, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axhline(+sigma_nmad, color=\"orange\", lw=1.2, ls=\"--\", label=f\"\u00b1sigma_NMAD\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axhline(-sigma_nmad, color=\"orange\", lw=1.2, ls=\"--\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axhline(+0.15,      color=\"red\",    lw=1.2, ls=\":\",  label=\"\u00b10.15 (outlier)\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axhline(-0.15,      color=\"red\",    lw=1.2, ls=\":\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_xlabel(\"z_real\"); axes[1, 1].set_ylabel(\"\u0394z / (1 + z)\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_title(\"(d) Residuos vs z_real\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_ylim(-0.3, 0.3)\n",
    "axes[1, 1].legend(fontsize=9, loc=\"upper right\")\n",
    "plt.colorbar(hb2, ax=axes[1, 1], label=\"# galaxias\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(plot_dir / \"model_final_summary.png\", dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(f\"Salvo: {plot_dir / 'model_final_summary.png'}\")\n"
   ]
